{"type":"finding","iteration":20,"focus":"S3-04","id":"finding:S3-04A:deferred-output-sink","summary":"Add a reusable deferred atomic output sink for clustered reducer writes.","reference":"external/kasper/src/state.ts:112-117 and external/kasper/src/state.ts:886-891","target":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/atomic-state.ts","integrationTarget":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/scripts/reduce-state.cjs","portDifficulty":"med","tag":"quick-win","why":"The reducer writes registry, strategy, and dashboard in one sync block; a queued sink can coalesce repeated renders while preserving reducer-owned outputs."}
{"type":"finding","iteration":20,"focus":"S3-04","id":"finding:S3-04B:versioned-no-drop-flush","summary":"Use per-path versions and dirty-again reflush to keep the last queued write.","reference":"external/kasper/src/state.ts:894-905 and external/kasper/src/state.ts:939-949","target":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/atomic-state.ts","portDifficulty":"med","tag":"quick-win","why":"Debounce without a captured-version check can strand a final content update that lands during an in-flight write."}
{"type":"finding","iteration":20,"focus":"S3-04","id":"finding:S3-04C:drain-required-before-exit","summary":"Require reducer callers to await drain or close before process exit.","reference":"external/kasper/src/state.ts:557-568, external/kasper/src/state.ts:610-615, and external/kasper/src/state.ts:920-930","target":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/atomic-state.ts","integrationTarget":".opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml","portDifficulty":"med","tag":"quick-win","why":"The workflow expects reducer outputs to exist immediately after reduce-state returns, so deferred writes must be drained before command completion."}
{"type":"finding","iteration":20,"focus":"S3-04","id":"finding:S3-04D:coalesce-repeated-paths-not-three-files","summary":"Coalescing reduces repeated writes per path, not one necessary write to each derived surface.","reference":"external/kasper/src/state.ts:1048-1059","target":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/atomic-state.ts","portDifficulty":"easy","tag":"quick-win","why":"Kasper writes one state object; our reducer writes three distinct files, so the API should dedupe superseded content per path rather than pretending three outputs become one."}
